.TH "batadv_send_unicast_skb" 9 "batadv_send_unicast_skb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_send_unicast_skb \- Send unicast packet to neighbor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" batadv_send_unicast_skb
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_neigh_node *neigh "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
packet to be transmitted (with batadv header and no outer eth header)
.IP "neigh" 12
neighbor which is used as next hop to destination
.SH "RETURN"
A negative errno code is returned on a failure. A success does not
guarantee the frame will be transmitted as it may be dropped due
to congestion or traffic shaping.
